<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-038-206 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 435 083</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Oct 7 1991 v25 n40 p68(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Persuasion: many features but lacks DDE. (Dynamic Data Exchange)(Aldus Corp.'s Persuasion 2.0 for Microsoft Corp. Windows 3.0)(includes related articles on product features and on vendorfinancial information) (Software Review) (Technology Analysis:Presentation Software) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Slater, Derek; Davidson, Lisa.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Aldus Corp's Aldus Persuasion 2.0 for Windows presentationsoftware package is priced at $495 and provides an extensive setof tools to create all types of presentations.andP;  The program forMicrosoft Windows 3.0 parallels its Apple Computer counterpartvery closely.andP;  It uses an outline feature to create slides, and itis equipped with charting features ranging from bulleted textcharts to organizational charts.andP;  Persuasion 2.0 is equipped witheditable clip art and outstanding color control, and it has ahandy slide sorter feature to organize presentations.andP;  Anotherbeneficial feature is strong screen show transition effects,including fades and wipes.andP;  Persuasion lacks built-in calculationtools.andP;  Some advanced curve-type graphics are lacking, and thereis no support provided for Dynamic Data Exchange.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Aldus Corp. (Products).andO;Product:   Aldus Persuasion 2.0 for Windows (Presentation software)(evaluation).andO;Topic:     EvaluationPresentation software.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Aldus Persuasion 2.0 for Windows. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>